news.title: Creaticity invests $1 million to set up 32,000 sq ft retail showroom for Index Living Mall
news.para: The partnership model involves Creaticity investing in store setup and operations, while ILM provides product, software and marketing support.

news.title: Asian Paints' net profit dips 43.71% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Asian Paints' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 8,201.09 crore in Q2 FY25, a dip of 5.12 per cent from Rs 8,643.77 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: UK's Vistry warns of further cost pressures in 2025 as shares drop 21%
news.para: Shares of Britain's largest homebuilder by yearly output slumped to a near 13-month low of 691 pence to be the top percentage loser on the FTSE 100 index after it flagged cost overruns in one of its divisions.

news.title: Rajasthan HC directs state govt to respond on haphazard construction of multi-storey buildings
news.para: A reply is required on the multi-storey building on 17,000 square metres of land of the proposed old Malviya Nagar Regional Engineering College (MREC) Campus and Officers' Residence near Gandhinagar Judges' Residence in Jaipur.

news.title: South Goa Advocates’ Association to seek revocation of hike in land rates
news.para: SGAA president Prasad Naik said that the new rates are a significant departure from historical adjustments, as the increase is four to five times the base rate.

news.title: Indore administration seals eight commercial establishments operating from basements
news.para: A joint team of district administration and municipal corporation led by SDM Ghanshyam Dhanghar sealed eight commercial establishments which were operating illegally from basements designated for parking.

news.title: Kanpur metro set for trial run from Moti Jheel to Kanpur Central in November 2024
news.para: Kanpur Metro currently operates on the Priority Corridor from IIT to Moti Jheel. This is a nine-km distance that the Metro covers. However, the day is fast approaching when city residents will be able to travel all the way up to Kanpur Central station.

news.title: Noida sees 16,500 property registrations in October 2024
news.para: Assistant inspector-general of registration Shashi Bhanu Mishra said the department mopped up a revenue of Rs 513.4 crore, about 22% more than the target of Rs 421.5 crore set for the month. This is a 101% year-over-year increase compared to the same period last year.

news.title: DTCP demolishes illegal colonies across 30 acres in Gurugram
news.para: The two-day drive, led by the enforcement wing with police support, targeted constructions in Gwal Pahari, Bhondsi, and Alipur villages.

news.title: GIC Housing Finance's net profit rises 20.97% in Q2 FY25
news.para: GIC Housing Finance's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 265.70 crore in Q2 FY25, a dip of 1.66 per cent from Rs 270.19 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Signatureglobal (India) posts net profit of Rs 4.15 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: Signatureglobal (India)'s net consolidated total income stood at Rs 777.42 crore in Q2 FY25 as against Rs 121.16 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Orient Cement reports 90.5% drop in profit to Rs 2.32 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: Its revenue from operations was down 24.5 per cent at Rs 544.02 crore during the quarter under review against Rs 720.57 crore in the corresponding period a year ago. Total expenses of OCL were at Rs 544.47 crore in the September quarter, down 20 per cent.

news.title: Puravankara posts net loss of Rs 17.06 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: Puravankara's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 519.68 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 36.20 per cent from Rs 381.57 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: House of Abhinandan Lodha to invest Rs 3,000 crore to expand into six cities
news.para: Mumbai-based The House of Abhinandan Lodha, which was formed in 2021, sells only residential plots across Maharashtra, Goa and Ayodhya in Uttar Pradesh.

news.title: India Cements loss widens to Rs 339 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: It had incurred a loss of Rs 80.07 crore in the July-September period a year ago, according to a BSE filing from ICL, in which rival Aditya Birla group firm UltraTech Cement has announced to acquire a majority stake.

news.title: Action Construction Equipment's net profit up 28.24% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Action Construction Equipment's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 790.90 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 14.59 per cent from Rs 690.21 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Anthurium Developers and GKW to jointly develop 37 acre land parcel in Mumbai’s Bhandup
news.para: This land parcel will have a development potential of around 3.6 million sq ft. It will be a mixed-use development with residential, commercial and retail components.

news.title: Spain's Inmocemento to make market debut valued at $2.1 billion
news.para: The company, which has 454.9 million shares, set a reference share price of 4.25 euros for its listing, according to a late Thursday filing to Spain's stock market regulator.

news.title: US's mortgage rates rises to 6.79% in November 2024
news.para: The average rate on the popular 30-year fixed-rate mortgage climbed to 6.79%, the highest level since July, from 6.72% last week, mortgage finance agency Freddie Mac said on Thursday.
